# .gitignore for a Unity 6 (6000.x) project.
#
# Commit Assets/, Packages/, ProjectSettings/ AND every .meta file.
# Ignore the regenerated/local folders below. The "exclude from version
# control" set is from the Unity manual (default-directories: Library, Temp,
# UserSettings are unique to a machine; AssetMetadata: .meta must be committed).
#
# Rename to ".gitignore" at the project root.

# --- Regenerated caches & local working dirs (NEVER commit) ---
/[Ll]ibrary/
/[Tt]emp/
/[Oo]bj/
/[Bb]uild/
/[Bb]uilds/
/[Ll]ogs/
/[Uu]ser[Ss]ettings/

# Asset Store / package download caches that may appear at the root
/[Mm]emoryCaptures/
/[Rr]ecordings/

# --- IDE / .NET solution files (regenerated by the editor's IDE integration) ---
# The .csproj and .sln are generated by Unity's IDE package on open; do not commit.
*.csproj
*.sln
*.user
*.suo
*.userprefs
*.unityproj
*.pidb
.vs/
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- OS / build cruft ---
.DS_Store
*.tmp
*.pyc

# --- Crash & build artifacts ---
sysinfo.txt
*.apk
*.aab
*.unitypackage
crashlytics-build.properties

# === DO commit (do NOT add these to .gitignore) ===
#   /Assets/  /Packages/  /ProjectSettings/
#   every *.meta file  — losing a .meta breaks all references to that asset.
